In re HARRIMAN SECURITIES CORPORATION, Bankrupt. LAND OBEROESTERREICH (UPPER PROVINCE OF AUSTRIA), Appellant, v. IRVING TRUST COMPANY, as Trustee in Bankruptcy, Appellee. No. 474. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 10, 1935. Wachtell, Manheim & Grouf, of New York City (Samuel R. Wachtell, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Zalkin & Cohen, of New York City (Israel Akselrod, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order (9 F.Supp. 860) affirmed on opinion below.
